    "common" : [ "<p>The kings of León studied on this page are descendants of Alfonso III, el Magno, king of Asturias, who transferred his capital to León (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('755c42c6-3be9-41fd-8655-22f8a6877215'); return false;\">Medieval Lands, <span id=\"htdate0\"></span></a>). The relationship between the kings of León and the Asturian kings is not hypothetical, unlike the supposed connection between the Visigothic and Asturian kings (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8389be3c-29ce-4d64-8577-7ed6d3f09a2b'); return false;\">History Tracers, <span id=\"htdate1\"></span></a>).</p>", "<p>When discussing the kings of León in his lineage book, Count Don Pedro does not differentiate between the Asturian and León kings, considering them all as kings of León (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('94cddc67-cec8-414a-9885-6d3e7ee952ba'); return false;\">Nobiliário Conde Dom Pedro, <span id=\"htdate2\"></span>, pp. 1 - 5</a>).</p>", "<p class=\"reflection\" id=\"myFirstReflection\"></p>", "<p>Knowledge never stops, and here we are not presenting the entire history of the Visigoth kings. To learn more about them, in addition to the chronicles and papers we mention, we suggest visiting the site Medieval Lands (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('755c42c6-3be9-41fd-8655-22f8a6877215'); return false;\">Medieval Lands, <span id=\"htdate3\"></span></a>).</p>" ],
    "families" : [
        {
            "id" : "588c52dc-7b48-490d-acb4-044f07314444",
            "name": "Kings of León",
            "history": [ "<p>The history begins with Ordoño II, son of Alfonso III. We follow chronicles contemporary to the kings to present the genealogy as close to the facts as possible.</p>", "<p>Regarding the ancestors of Alfonso III, the Great, Count Don Pedro suggests a lineage (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('94cddc67-cec8-414a-9885-6d3e7ee952ba'); return false;\">Nobiliário Conde Dom Pedro, <span id=\"htdate4\"></span>, pp. 1 - 5</a>) which is incompatible with the chronicles, thus we treat it as hypothetical. On the other hand, Medieval Lands follows the ancestors according to the chronicles (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('755c42c6-3be9-41fd-8655-22f8a6877215'); return false;\">Medieval Lands, <span id=\"htdate5\"></span></a>).</p>" ],
