                {
                    "id" : "539e6b5a-55de-46e9-bcc0-d1f42440bb21",
                    "name": "Ordoño",
                    "history" : [ "<p>When his father passed away, Ordoño began to rule the kingdom as Ordoño III in the year <span id=\"htdate72\"></span>.</p>", "<p>During his reign, like his father, he engaged in new wars against the Muslims. After victories by Count Fernán Gonzáles in <span id=\"htdate73\"></span>, the king sacked Lisbon and secured an advantageous peace with the caliph (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('2365a881-17ba-4719-96fe-7cf753f2a475'); return false;\">Brito, Bernardo de, <span id=\"htdate74\"></span>, fl. 386 - 389</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('755c42c6-3be9-41fd-8655-22f8a6877215'); return false;\">Medieval Lands, <span id=\"htdate75\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('09ea5f66-72f5-4844-844b-525f107930a6'); return false;\">Sevilla-Quiñones, Margarida T, Real Academia de la História</a>).</p>", "<p>Ordoño had only one son, but it is not possible to confirm if the mother was his wife Urraca. There is also the possibility that the son was the child of a daughter of Pelayo Gutierrez (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('755c42c6-3be9-41fd-8655-22f8a6877215'); return false;\">Medieval Lands, <span id=\"htdate76\"></span></a>). Given this scenario, we will include two [possible] wives and connect the son to an Unknown person.</p>" ],
